The '''2024 Atlantic Coast Conference football season''', part of the [[2024 NCAA Division I FBS football season]], was the 72nd season of [[college football]] play for the [[Atlantic Coast Conference]] (ACC). This was the ACC's first season with 17 members, after the additions of [[2024 California Golden Bears football team|California]], [[SMU Mustangs football|SMU]], and [[Stanford Cardinal football|Stanford]].  The entire schedule was released on January 24, 2024.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |date=2024-01-24 |title=ACC Unveils Complete 2024 Football Schedule |url=http://theacc.com/news/2024/1/24/acc-unveils-complete-2024-football-schedule.aspx |access-date=2024-04-01 |website=theacc.com |language=en}}</ref>

[[2024 SMU Mustangs football team|SMU]] finished as regular season champions with a perfect 8–0 conference record. [[2024 Clemson Tigers football team|Clemson]] finished second with a 7–1 conference record. Clemson prevailed in the [[2024 ACC Championship Game|Championship Game]] 34–31. Both Clemson and SMU were selected to the [[2024–25 College Football Playoff|College Football Playoff]] and eleven other teams qualified for [[2024–25 NCAA football bowl games|bowl games]]. The ACC was tied with the [[Southeastern Conference|SEC]] for the conference with the most bowl participants as both conferences had thirteen teams qualifying for bowl games. However, the bowl season did not proceed well for the ACC, as they finished a collective 2–11 in bowl games. Their .154 winning percentage was the lowest of conferences sending more than one team to bowl games.

