== Head coaches ==

=== Pre-season changes ===
[[Syracuse Orange football|Syracuse]] head coach [[Dino Babers]] was fired during the 2023 season.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-11-19 |title=Syracuse fires coach Babers after eight seasons |url=https://www.espn.com/college-football/story/_/id/38935092/sources-syracuse-fires-coach-dino-babers-eight-seasons |access-date=2024-04-01 |website=ESPN.com |language=en|author=Thamel, Pete}}</ref> On November 28, 2023, [[Georgia Bulldogs football|Georgia]] defensive backs coach, [[Fran Brown]], was hired as his replacement.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Fran Brown, Nation’s No. 1 Recruiter, Tapped to Lead Orange Football |url=https://cuse.com/news/2023/11/28/syracuse-university-taps-fran-brown-nations-no-1-recruiter-to-lead-orange-football |access-date=2024-04-01 |website=Syracuse University Athletics |language=en}}</ref>

[[Texas A&M Aggies football|Texas A&M]] hired [[Duke Blue Devils football|Duke]] head coach [[Mike Elko]] to replace [[Jimbo Fisher]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Wilburn |first=Caroline |date=2023-11-27 |title=Texas A&M names Mike Elko as new head football coach |url=https://www.texastribune.org/2023/11/27/texas-am-football-mike-elko/ |access-date=2024-04-01 |website=The Texas Tribune |language=en}}</ref> On December 7, 2023, he was replaced by [[Manny Diaz (American football)|Manny Diaz]], [[2023 Penn State Nittany Lions football team|Penn State's]] defensive coordinator and linebackers coach.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-12-07 |title=Duke Names Manny Diaz Head Football Coach |url=https://goduke.com/news/2023/12/7/duke-names-manny-diaz-head-football-coach.aspx |access-date=2024-04-01 |website=Duke University |language=en}}</ref>

[[Boston College Eagles football|Boston College's]] [[Jeff Hafley]] was hired as the [[Green Bay Packers]] defensive coordinator on January 31, 2024.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Packers name Jeff Hafley defensive coordinator |url=https://www.packers.com/news/packers-name-jeff-hafley-defensive-coordinator |access-date=2024-04-01 |website=packers.com |language=en-US}}</ref> On February 9, 2024, [[Bill O'Brien (American football)|Bill O'Brien]] was announced as Boston College's new head coach.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Bill O'Brien - Football Coach |url=https://bceagles.com/sports/football/roster/coaches/bill-o-brien/2505 |access-date=2024-04-01 |website=Boston College Athletics |language=en}}</ref>

